{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 23:56:34.470734", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- The Clos/EBGP routing fabric is healthy end-to-end (leaves, spines, super-spine have established BGP sessions and have correct routing for leaf host subnets).\\n- East–west host connectivity is partially unavailable because host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24) is down. This is the root cause of failed reachability to 10.0.1.2.\\n- The access link on leaf_router_0_1 toward its host VLAN/interface is up, but there is no ARP/neigh entry for 10.0.1.2 and pings fail—consistent with the endpoint being offline.\\n\\nFindings and evidence\\n\\n1) Host access-layer status\\n- pc_0_0 network config:\\n  - IP: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0). Routing table and interface are correct.\\n- pc_0_1 status:\\n  - Tools error indicates container not running:\\n    - “container ... is not running” (HTTP 409 Conflict). This confirms the host endpoint is down/offline.\\n\\n2) Control-plane health (BGP)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) and leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): BGP summary shows all neighbors Established with received prefixes populated.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): BGP sessions Established to super-spine and to leafs; full set of leaf subnets appear in RIB.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): BGP Established to spines; learning leaf subnets as expected.\\n- Routing tables:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: C 10.0.0.0/24; B 10.0.1.0/24 via uplink (172.16.1.0). Multiple remote /24s learned via BGP as expected.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: C 10.0.1.0/24; B 10.0.0.0/24 via uplink (172.16.1.2). Upstream spines and super-spine have consistent BGP routes for both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- Assessment: Control plane is converged and correct. No BGP adjacency or route distribution anomalies observed.\\n\\n3) Data-plane tests\\n- From pc_0_0:\\n  - Ping default GW (10.0.0.1): success (0% loss).\\n  - Ping remote leaf SVI (10.0.1.1): success (0% loss, ttl=62), proving fabric forwarding between pods/tiers is working.\\n  - Ping remote host (10.0.1.2): 100% packet loss (no replies).\\n- From leaf_router_0_1 toward its access subnet:\\n  - Interface eth8: UP, LOWER_UP.\\n  - ip neigh show dev eth8: no entry for 10.0.1.2 (blank), and ping 10.0.1.2 from the leaf fails (100% loss). This indicates ARP is not resolving because the host is not present/responding.\\n  - ip r get 10.0.1.2 resolves to dev eth8 with src 10.0.1.1 (connected), so routing is correct; failure is at L2/endpoint.\\n\\n4) Minor observation\\n- leaf_router_0_0 shows neighbor entry “10.0.0.2 lladdr … DELAY.” Despite this transient neighbor state, pings to/from 10.0.0.2 succeed, so no impact observed. Likely normal neighbor cache behavior.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Failure domain: Access segment on pod 0 leaf 1 (10.0.1.0/24) toward the host.\\n- Last reachable point: leaf_router_0_1 SVI 10.0.1.1 is reachable from the fabric and from remote host’s pod.\\n- Unreachable endpoint: 10.0.1.2 (pc_0_1).\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Host pc_0_1 is down (container not running). Consequently, ARP resolution for 10.0.1.2 fails on leaf_router_0_1 and ICMP to 10.0.1.2 fails from both the leaf and remote host.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- Any traffic destined to 10.0.1.2 fails. The rest of the fabric and other prefixes appear unaffected; cross-pod routing (e.g., to 10.0.1.1 and other learned /24s) is operational. No evidence of broader control-plane or fabric data-plane impairment., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='77dd76c8-72a3-4096-b9d1-71aaabf91591'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
